-- Institutional securities loss hits Morgan Stanley profit 
-- By Tanya Agrawal in Bangalore
-- Fri Jan 17, 2014 07:26AM EST
-- None



Jan 17 (Reuters) - Morgan Stanley <MS.N> reported a sharp fall in quarterly profit as the Wall Street bank posted a pre-tax loss of $1.1 billion from continuing operations in its institutional securities business.

Net income from continuing operations applicable to the company fell to $192 million, or 7 cents per share, in the fourth quarter from $661 million, or 33 cents per share, in the same quarter of 2012, the bank said on Friday. [ID:nBw9nJFzga]   (Reporting by Tanya Agrawal in Bangalore; tanya.agrawal@thomsonreuters.com; within U.S. +1 646 223 8780; outside U.S. +91 80 6749 1130; Reuters Messaging: tanya.agrawal.thomsonreuters.com@reuters.net)  Keywords: MORGANSTANLEY RESULTS/